After completion of [[Secrets of the North]], the [[Strange Creature]] can be fought again in the form of a [[Phantom Muspah]] (aka, "Muspah"). This time, it is stronger.

== Requirements ==
* Completion of {{SCP|Quest}} [[Secrets of the North]] to access the [[Ghorrock Dungeon]]

== Suggested skills ==
* {{SCP|Ranged|85+}} 
* {{SCP|Magic|85+}} (if using magic)
* {{SCP|Defence|75+}} 
* {{SCP|Prayer|74+}} for [[Rigour]]  (77+ for [[Augury]])
* {{SCP|Construction|82+}} for [[Ornate rejuvenation pool]] (with boost) or completion of the elite [[Desert diary]] for [[Desert Amulet 4]]
* {{SCP|Herblore|81+}} for [[Surge potion|Surge potions]] (optional)

==Transportation==
The quickest methods of reaching [[Weiss]], where the Phantom Muspah resides, are:
*Using the [[ring of shadows]] to teleport to [[Ghorrock Dungeon]]. Requires completion of [[Desert Treasure II - The Fallen Empire]] and the [[frozen tablet]], obtained from [[Duke Sucellus]].
*Using an [[icy basalt]]. Go through the gap in the fence.
*Using the Weiss teleport in the [[portal chamber]] or [[portal nexus]] of a player-owned house.
*Using [[Larry]]'s boat north-east of [[Rellekka]] and sailing to Weiss from there. [[Fairy ring]] code {{Fairycode|DKS}} is the closest teleport to Larry's boat.
Once in Weiss, enter the [[salt mine]] (accessible from the staircase in Snowflake and My Arm's hut) and go deeper into the cave to enter the [[Ghorrock Dungeon]]. Then, run south.

==Forms==
Throughout the fight, the [[Phantom Muspah]] will switch forms after taking 100 damage in the Ranged form (barring the teleport attack) and 80 damage in the Melee form. Thrall damage does not count towards these damage thresholds (with the exception of the final stand transformation when the boss reaches ≤127 hitpoints). 

During transformations, Muspah will slam the ground and spawn spikes around the arena. Always remember that a spike will always appear on the player's current position when Muspah transforms. Standing on a spike will knock the player back to a clear tile and heal the boss for ~75% of the damage dealt.

Muspah's defence can be reduced down to 125. The defence reduction will preserve between phases until the shielded phase, where Muspah's defence resets to 200.

===Ranged===
[[File:Phantom Muspah (ranged).png|left|180px|Ranged]]
Muspah's '''{{Colour|green|Ranged}}''' form will attack with [[ranged]], occasionally [[magic]], and has a significantly lower [[Ranged Defence|ranged defence]] bonus compared to its [[magic defence]] bonus.

'''{{Colour|green|Ranged}}''' attacks are more common and calculated on attack start, therefore [[Protect from Missiles]] should remain active by default. This can deal up to 61 damage.

Occasionally, Muspah will charge up for a '''{{Color|blue|Magic}}''' attack, appearing to stand up and charge a purple orb before launching it at the player. It is imperative to swap to [[Protect from Magic]] '''immediately''' upon seeing this animation, as failing to do so can result in taking up to 72 damage. This will also apply [[Corruption (status)|corruption]] onto the player.

Unlike the other attacks, using Protect from Magic while the projectile is in transit will reduce a significant amount of damage, but the player will still be inflicted corruption.

'''Corruption'''  

Taking damage from the '''{{Color|blue|Magic}}''' attack will also apply [[corruption (status)|corruption]] onto the player that drains 3, 6, and 9 [[prayer points]] every 6 seconds, for a total of 18 prayer points over the course of 18 seconds. Players can cast [[Ward of Arceuus]] to become temporarily immune to being corrupted, or to nullify its effect after the fact. [[Ward of Arceuus]] is cheaper than a dose of [[Super restore]], but 1 additional inventory spot for runes will take up more inventory per use unless a player is hit by 8 or more [[corruption (status)|corruption]] effects per trip.  

{{clear|left}}
===Melee===
[[File:Phantom Muspah (melee).png|left|180px]]
[[File:Phantom Muspah - stepback method.mp4|thumb|400px|A player demonstrating the stepback method with a metronome that beats every [[tick]] (0.6 seconds). Once the player takes a hit from Muspah, click one tile away from it on the third tick.]]
Muspah's '''{{Colour|maroon|Melee}}''' form will deal significantly increased melee damage the longer it stays still. It is imperative to maintain distance at all times and do not allow Muspah to chain melee hits. Muspah's melee hit can deal up to 34 damage.

Players can avoid its melee attack entirely if praying melee and Muspah was chasing one tick before the intended attack tick. This led to what is known as the step-back method, which involves moving away from the boss one tick before the intended attack, as seen in the demonstration to the right. Below is a breakdown of events on each tick of a step-back method being executed during Muspah's 5-tick melee cycle.

# '''''Muspah hitsplats player'''''  
# ''(hitsplat fades)'' 
# ''(nothing)'' 
# ''Click to step 1 tile away'' 
# Player movement executed 
# '''''Muspah will chase and attack player same tick,  for 0 damage if protect from melee is active'''''{{clear|left}}

Muspah has a significantly lower magic defence bonus in the form compared to its ranged defence bonus.

For lower-level players who are struggling to freeze it, Muspah can be [[Safespot#Kiting|kited]] and attacked with ranged to avoid damage from its melee form, similar to kiting Commander Zilyana. However, due to the Muspah’s larger size, an “octagon” run pattern works better than running in a square.

===Shielded===
[[File:Phantom Muspah (shielded).png|left|180px]]
Muspah's '''{{Colour|teal|Shielded}}''' form is a reinforced '''{{Colour|green|Ranged}}''' form that is immune to all regular sources of damage. This reinforced form reverts back to the normal '''{{Colour|green|Ranged}}''' form when the prayer shield is removed. Prayer-draining attacks such as [[Smite]], [[Corruption spells]], and [[Sapphire bolts (e)|enchanted sapphire bolts]] will drain the shield faster.
{{clear|left}}

==Fight overview==
{{Tile markers box|Module:Tile markers/Phantom Muspah.json}}
The Phantom Muspah can spawn in ranged or melee form, and will trigger special attacks at 75% and 50% health. Ranged spawns will trigger Lightning clouds at 75%, melee spawns will trigger homing spikes at 75%. The unused special will always occur at 50% health.

*Players may deal large hits at the end of a ranged form, which will count towards ending the melee form.
*Hitting Muspah below 637 HP before hitting under 650 HP prevents Muspah from entering ranged form before his lightning cloud special attack. This allows you a full 100 damage against range form instead of switching to melee immediately after.
*Large amounts of damage dealt during the lightning cloud special attack will likely skip the entirety of the final melee phase.
*'''Lightning Clouds''' -  Muspah will rapidly teleport around the arena and spawn lightning clouds that travel across the area. 
** Getting hit by a cloud will deal up to 20 damage, though they can be avoided by standing on a specific tile, provided with the button above. Players should avoid standing on this tile until the attack occurs, so that spikes aren't protruding on it.
** Muspah will always appear to the north-east when the move is finished.
** Muspah has combat stats equal to Range form, and can be attacked during this phase.
** Damage dealt during this phase '''does not''' count towards the damage threshold for a form swap.
*'''Homing Spikes''' - The Phantom Muspah will slam the ground, causing 2-4 spikes to home in on the player.  
** Players can stand behind hardened spikes to avoid the homing spikes from reaching them if there's more than one spike grouped together.
** The spikes move 1 tile per 2 ticks, do not move diagonally, and cannot pass through idle spikes.
** After ~20 seconds, the spikes harden and stop moving.
** Spikes that are directly adjacent to the player and under the Phantom Muspah will never be chosen to home in on the player.
