===Shielded phase===
Upon reaching less than 127 health, Muspah will teleport to the centre of the arena and unleash a massive shockwave that engulfs the entire arena. Players must stand behind a spike to avoid the attack, or it will deal up to 80 damage and the subsequent corruption will drain more prayer points compared to its magic attack. Players can place spikes on 8 specific tiles (also provided with the above button) to block the shockwave most efficiently. Spikes being on all 8 tiles is unlikely, but would completely negate a shockwave. Once Muspah finishes the attack, it will change into its shielded form, activating a prayer shield and [[Soul Split]], as well as increasing the max hit and accuracy of its attacks.
[[File:Phantom Muspah - prayer flicking.mp4|thumb|400px|The player adjusts their timing to attack Muspah after it attacks, so that they can activate Smite to deplete the prayer shield quicker without risk of being attacked without protection prayers.]]

The prayer shield has 75 health, and is drained by 2 after each attack. The [[Phantom Muspah]] will also heal itself for 50% of the damage inflicted, rounded down to the nearest whole number; e.g., a hit of 23 will cause it to heal 11 health. The player can further speed up the drain by using various prayer-draining methods, such as the [[Smite]] prayer or having a [[corruption spell]] active. 

Using a crossbow with [[Sapphire bolts (e)|enchanted sapphire bolts]] or [[sapphire dragon bolts (e)|enchanted sapphire dragon bolts]] is highly recommended, as they have a 25% chance (27.5% with completion of the [[Hard Kandarin Diary]]){{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/jagexash/status/1633115030588731395|date=7 March 2023|archiveurl=https://archive.ph/bt0xu|archivedate=7 March 2023|quote=I think it'd be based on 25% (plus diary buffs) for any eligible NPC *if* you pass the accuracy/defence roll first.}} to activate their special effect against the prayer shield, draining around 33 prayer from it.

To successfully use Smite, players should avoid lining up their attacks with Muspah's ranged or magic attacks. Players can utilize the following five-tick cycle to determine when they can use Smite:

* '''Tick 1''': Muspah's ranged attack damage is calculated (Protect from Ranged must be active on this tick to reduce damage)
* '''Tick 2:''' Empty (can use Smite)
* '''Tick 3''': Empty (can use Smite)
* '''Tick 4''': Muspah's magic attack damage is calculated (Protect from Magic must be active on this tick to avoid damage)
* '''Tick 5''': Empty (can use Smite)

If the player is using a weapon with a five-tick attack speed, such as a crossbow on rapid, attacking Muspah on the first possible tick of the shielded phase will ensure that the player always attacks on Tick 2 of the above cycle, allowing them to flick Smite consistently. If players find themselves attacking on Tick 1 or Tick 4 of the cycle, it is advisable to delay their next attack by one tick to offset their attacks.

Note that because this attack cycle is one tick faster than in previous phases, there is one less tick between a magic attack landing and the next ranged attack being calculated. As a result, players should be prepared to switch prayers quickly after a magic projectile hits them. 

Once the shield is depleted, Muspah will return to its ranged form—though still with a five-tick attack speed—and create a large number of spikes (including one on the player's position) before resuming combat as normal. The spikes will emerge every four attacks and cover more tiles, growing from existing clusters of spikes.

====Shield Skip====
For players attempting [[Phantom Muspah Speed-Runner]], it is possible to bypass the shielded phase entirely. If Muspah's health reaches zero before the shield is applied, the shield phase is cancelled and Muspah instead restores 1 health. [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SEjWqdcQeIE <nowiki>[Youtube]</nowiki>]

To succeed in a shield skip:

* There is a 5-tick vulnerability between Muspah's teleport and shield application. 3-tick and 4-tick weapons can deliver two attacks in this timeframe.
* When Muspah teleports to the middle, you must be standing within 1-2 tiles of Muspah's 5x5 to prevent delays on ranged weapon damage [https://youtu.be/0PM3xUGMLhA&t=21 <nowiki>[Youtube]</nowiki>].
* Spam click to attack (Clicking before vulnerability will be lost, and will not cause a delayed attack at first vulnerability)
* Your first attack will land before the shockwave
* Your second and final attack will come after the shockwave
* If Muspah is at 0 Health pending a successful shield skip, '''any further damage will fail the shield skip (ex: Thralls).'''
* If successful, Muspah will not enter the shield phase, but exit with 1 health to be killed easily.

This skip requires 2 or 3 lucky hits, and is therefore very luck dependent.

# The hit which brings Muspah below 127 health is the most critical. If a player is unlucky and hits Muspah from 135 to 126, players must deal a full 126 damage in the hits to follow. Oppositely, if a player is lucky and hits 80 damage from 130 health down to 50, the player has two hits to deal only 50 damage.
# The first hit after Muspah teleports.
# If hit 2 did not bring Muspah to 0 health, the hit following the shockwave must do so.

==Equipment==
Ideally, use both [[Ranged]] and [[Magic]], to exploit the weaknesses of both forms. Camping a single form will result in greatly increased kill times, with range camp generally being slightly more optimal. To a lesser extent, Magic-only setups with best-in-slot mage gear and a Tumeken's shadow are doable; a ranged swap may still be helpful for Muspah's smite phase.

Ranged setups employing ZCB specs benefit greatly from using [[Surge potion|Surge potions]].

The [[Arceuus spellbook]] is particularly useful against Muspah, and is strongly recommended. In addition to the use of [[thralls]], [[Greater Corruption]] can be used for additional damage against Muspah's prayer shield. [[Ward of Arceuus]] can be used to protect the player from [[Corruption (status)|corruption]]. [[Vile Vigour]] can be used for additional run energy. [[Death Charge]] can be procced off Muspah to restore additional special attack energy, if not resetting between kills.

However, some players opt to use [[Ancient Magicks]] or [[Standard spellbook]] to simply freeze with [[Ice spells]] or [[Entangle]] Muspah to avoid its melee attack. Freezing the Muspah also makes the faster attack speed of the [[Eye of ayak]] easier to take advantage of. Standard spellbook gives access to [[Wind spells]], which Muspah is weak to.

